{"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/spooktacularkit"]}],"sections":[],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit"},"abstract":[{"text":"Create and manage macOS virtual machines on Apple Silicon.","type":"text"}],"metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"SpooktacularKit"}],"title":"SpooktacularKit","externalID":"SpooktacularKit","symbolKind":"module","roleHeading":"Framework","role":"collection"},"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"hierarchy":{"paths":[[]]},"topicSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/GettingStarted","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/CLIReference","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/GitHubActionsGuide","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/JenkinsGuide","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/EC2MacDeployment","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/KubernetesGuide","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/MLWorkloads","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/RemoteDesktop","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/OpenClawGuide","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/BlueBubblesGuide","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/Versioning"],"title":"Guides","anchor":"Guides"}],"kind":"symbol","primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"anchor":"Overview","level":2,"text":"Overview","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"SpooktacularKit is the core library powering Spooktacular — a lightweight","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"macOS app for running macOS virtual machines. Built on Apple’s","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/virtualization","type":"reference"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"framework, it provides a Swift API for VM lifecycle management,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"IPSW installation, instant APFS cloning, and enterprise provisioning.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Use SpooktacularKit directly in your Swift project, or interact with it","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"through the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"spook"},{"text":" CLI, the Spooktacular GUI app, or the Kubernetes","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"operator. All interfaces share the same library and produce identical","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"behavior.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"name":"Important","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"SpooktacularKit requires an Apple Silicon Mac (M1 or later)","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"running macOS 14.0 (Sonoma) or later.","type":"text"}]}],"style":"important","type":"aside"},{"anchor":"Design-Principles","level":3,"text":"Design Principles","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"SpooktacularKit follows Apple’s Virtualization framework sample code","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"patterns exactly:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Direct use of "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"VZVirtualMachine"},{"type":"text","text":" — no unnecessary abstractions"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Value types ("},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"VirtualMachineSpecification"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"VirtualMachineMetadata"},{"type":"text","text":","},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"NetworkMode"},{"type":"text","text":") for all configuration"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Sendable"},{"type":"text","text":" conformance throughout for Swift 6 strict concurrency"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Full DocC documentation on every public API"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"anchor":"Creating-a-Virtual-Machine","level":3,"text":"Creating a Virtual Machine","type":"heading"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["import SpooktacularKit","","\/\/ Create a VM bundle with a hardware specification.","let spec = VirtualMachineSpecification(","    cpuCount: 8,","    memorySizeInBytes: 16 * 1024 * 1024 * 1024",")","let bundle = try VirtualMachineBundle.create(at: bundleURL, spec: spec)","","\/\/ Clone the bundle instantly using APFS copy-on-write.","let clone = try CloneManager.clone(source: bundle, to: cloneURL)","","\/\/ Build a Virtualization framework configuration.","let config = VZVirtualMachineConfiguration()","try VirtualMachineConfiguration.applySpec(spec, to: config)"]}],"kind":"content"}],"references":{"doc://SpooktacularKit/documentation/SpooktacularKit/GettingStarted":{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Create your first macOS virtual machine in minutes."}],"role":"collectionGroup","url":"\/documentation\/spooktacularkit\/gettingstarted","identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/GettingStarted","kind":"article","title":"Getting Started with Spooktacular","type":"topic"},"doc://SpooktacularKit/documentation/SpooktacularKit/BlueBubblesGuide":{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Set up a BlueBubbles iMessage server in a macOS VM — a dramatically simpler alternative to VMware on Windows."}],"role":"collectionGroup","url":"\/documentation\/spooktacularkit\/bluebubblesguide","identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/BlueBubblesGuide","kind":"article","title":"Running BlueBubbles iMessage Server","type":"topic"},"doc://SpooktacularKit/documentation/SpooktacularKit/MLWorkloads":{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Run ML training and inference on Apple Silicon GPUs inside Spooktacular virtual machines."}]